## Next Steps for Your Team

### 1. Environment Setup
Create a `.env.local` file with the following variables:
```env
# Supabase
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=your_supabase_url
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_supabase_anon_key
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your_service_role_key

# Stripe
NEXT_PUBLIC_STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=your_stripe_publishable_key
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=your_stripe_secret_key
STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=your_webhook_secret

# App
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=http://localhost:3000
```

### 2. Install Dependencies
You'll need to install additional packages:
```bash
npm install @supabase/supabase-js @supabase/ssr
npm install zustand  # For state management
npm install stripe @stripe/stripe-js
```

### 3. Database Setup
1. Create a Supabase project
2. Run the SQL files in this order:
   - [database/enums.sql](file:///c:/web-deloyed/Fashion/my-app/database/enums.sql)
   - [database/schema.sql](file:///c:/web-deloyed/Fashion/my-app/database/schema.sql)
   - [database/triggers.sql](file:///c:/web-deloyed/Fashion/my-app/database/triggers.sql)
   - [database/policies.sql](file:///c:/web-deloyed/Fashion/my-app/database/policies.sql)
   - [database/functions.sql](file:///c:/web-deloyed/Fashion/my-app/database/functions.sql)
   - [database/seed.sql](file:///c:/web-deloyed/Fashion/my-app/database/seed.sql) (optional, for sample data)

### 4. Generate Database Types
```bash
npx supabase gen types typescript --project-id YOUR_PROJECT_ID > types/database.types.ts
```

